  <preface xml:id="instructor-notes">
    <title>For Instructors</title>
    <xi:include href="../../../common/TBIL.ptx"/>
    <paragraphs xml:id="extra-features">
      <title>Features of the text</title>
      <p>
        Each section of this text also includes a brief set of Warm Up activities before the Class Activities,
        and follows them with Individual Practice.  Some instructors use only the Class Activities, while
        others assign their students to complete the Warm Up and Individual Practice activities 
        before and after class, respectively.
      </p>
      <p>
        This text also includes Mathematical Writing Explorations at the end of each section.
        These are used by some instructors to help their students gain experience with
        writing some proofs.  
      </p>
      <p>
        Instructors should begin with the intention of having students collaboratively
        solve the Class Activities (during synchronous meeting times), and pick and choose
        from the other parts as suits their instructional needs.  We have seen the complete range
        from some instructors using only the Class Activities to others using all parts
        due to varying instructional contexts.
      </p>
      <p component="print">
        This book is also freely available in HTML form at <url href="https://tbil.org" visual="tbil.org"/>. 
        We have endeavored to keep this print version aligned as closely as possible
        with the HTML version, with any deviations due to practical necessities.
        The HTML version includes some additional features such as interactive applets,
        embedded code cells for matrix computations, and hyperlinks to readiness resources.
      </p>
    </paragraphs>

    <xi:include href="../../../common/instructor-version.ptx"/>
    <xi:include href="../../../common/community.ptx"/>

